<ce:para>A large quantity of data, information, and knowledge are generated and accessed over the life cycle of a chemical product, from molecule discovery to process development to scale-up and production. Organizing this knowledge and making it available to support decisions has been a challenge due to its quantity, complexity, and the hierarchical data usage structure. This paper presents the functionality and technical details of a workflow-based knowledge management system and demonstrates its use in supporting the operation of a pilot plant for manufacturing liquid-based drug products. Â© 2014 Elsevier B.V.</ce:para>
